<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-148] Old syntax for specifying system properties should still be supported</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-148</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The old syntax is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;property&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;name&amp;gt;myprop&amp;lt;/name&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;value&amp;gt;myvalue&amp;lt;/value&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/property&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;New syntax (the one currently in SVN trunk):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;myprop&amp;gt;myvalue&amp;lt;/myprop&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I much prefer the new compact syntax but we should offer backward compatibility for existing users.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please keep the new syntax somehow though (I&apos;ve modified my builds to use it and I would hate to have to go back to the old syntax! &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</description>
